          elaboration: 'Pairs share their written methods (or lack of them) and give AQS feedback: Affirm the correct answer, Question the method, Suggest a step that could be added.',
          theoryKey: 'AQS_Feedback',
          tradeoff: 'Peer feedback surfaces more methods than a whole-class discussion — but students with no written method (like Siti) have nothing to share, and weak methods may go unchallenged.'
        }
      ]
    },
    B: {
      consequence: 'Rajan skips the prompt card and works independently. Nur fills in the blanks minimally — she has the right numbers but has not engaged with the "why." Wei Jie works through the steps slowly and carefully. Siti copies the prompt card structure but fills in the numbers without understanding them. The processes are now visible — but they are shallow. 19 minutes remain.',
      choices: [
        {
          id: '1',
          label: 'IRF probe on the scaffold steps',
          elaboration: 'Pause the class. Ask: "Why is Step 2 written as an equation? What would happen if you skipped it?" Use an IRF chain to probe four students who used the scaffold.',
          theoryKey: 'IRF_Chains',
          tradeoff: 'Deepens the visible thinking by asking students to justify the steps — but Rajan, who skipped the scaffold, is not included, and Siti may freeze under direct questioning.'
        },
