      tradeoff: 'Peer feedback activates the expertise in the room and produces real gains for Nur and Wei Jie. But Rajan is under-challenged and Siti is receiving rather than producing.',
      reflection: 'Describe: You used AQS peer feedback to address the calculation errors. Nur and Wei Jie made real gains through structured peer support.\n\nCompare: Peer feedback is more personalised than a whole-class reteach — but it depends on the quality of the peer explanation. A brief model of what good AQS feedback looks like might have made the exchange more precise.\n\nCritical: How do you design peer support so that both the helper and the helped are learning? What would Rajan need to make this a genuine learning experience for him too?'
